{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      Hybrid: Orchestrator + Guardrails\n      An orchestrator agent with structured validation at each step.\n      Combines A and B. A Claw orchestrator agent handles the chat and reasoning, but agent creation goes through a validated pipeline: (1) Orchestrator expands prompt → validated against schema, (2) Orchestrator generates agent spec → validated for completeness, (3) Code generation for workers → validated/tested, (4) Deploy via SDK. The orchestrator is free to reason, but its outputs are guardrailed at each stage. For management (signal, schedule, monitor), the orchestrator has deterministic tools.\n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            Best of both — flexible reasoning with reliable outputs\n            Guardrails catch hallucinated agent specs before deployment\n            Management actions are deterministic tools (no LLM in the loop)\n            Agentspan's own guardrail system enforces the validation\n            Natural fit — Agentspan already supports guardrails natively\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            More upfront design to define guardrail boundaries\n            Slightly more complex than pure A or pure B","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1776018120216}
